Manchester United have confirmed that midfielder, Donny van de Beek, has left the club to join Frank Lampard’s Everton on loan. Man United made the announcement in a statement via their website on transfer deadline day. Van de Beek will spend the remainder of the season at Everton. “Manchester United midfielder Donny van de Beek has agreed to join Premier League club Everton on loan until the end of the season,” Man United’s statement read. Van de Beek signed for Man United from Ajax during the summer of 2020. The Netherlands international made 50 appearances across all competitions since then, scoring two goals in the process.